Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Sheryl Cooper (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Sheryl Cooper (pictured) and her daughter Calico "beheaded" Sheryl's husband in front of a live audience?

entry.title: The Redbury New York (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the hotel The Redbury New York did not accept men for 95 years?

entry.title: Anthony Vaz (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Anthony Vaz was the first flag bearer and team captain for Kenya at the Olympics?

entry.title: Caleb Grimshaw (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Caleb Grimshaw sank after catching on fire, leaving at least 90 of the 457 people on board dead?

entry.title: Robert Hale (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that when Robert Hale performed as Wagner's Wotan in Washington, a reviewer noted that he commanded "the spirit, from tragic grandeur to ironic detachment, from flooding tenderness to grim rage"?

entry.title: The Sims 2: Bon Voyage (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a woman who bought The Sims 2: Bon Voyage sued its publisher?

entry.title: Chōsen shinpō (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the first newspaper in Korea, the Chōsen shinpō, was written in Japanese and Classical Chinese?

entry.title: a radio station in Alberta (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a radio station in Alberta fell afoul of Canadian content guidelines because new songs by Anne Murray were not Canadian enough?
